10:23 am  Court in session.  Case called.  Probation Agent Cassandra Botica.  Defendant Justin W Prescott appeared, Zeke S Wiedenfeld appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court notes defendant has not paid any of the restitution.  Ms. Botica does not believe defendant has made a good faith effort.  Atty Wiedenfeld makes record as to compliance with victims rights.  He is requesting an extension of probation.  Mr. Prescott  has been in recovery from heroin addition.  He did recently receive a promotion at work giving him the opportunity to get his head above water.  Court does not believe up until now he has made a good faith effort.  Court will extend probation for 2 years.  If he gets it paid off earlier than the 2 years, defendant can discharge from probation.  DA Wiedenfeld will prepare an Order for extension for court.

9:08 a.m.  Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given.  
Defendant Justin W Prescott in court with Attorney Francis R. Lettenberger.  
Valerian A Powell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Asst. Corp. Counsel Peter Navis appears on behalf of Walworth County.  
Matter is before the Court on the Defendant's Motion to Modify Conditions of Probation.  
The Motion challenges the Court's procedure in revoking the Defendant's Huber privileges without a hearing.  
Court hears argument of Attorneys.  
Court finds that huber is clearly a privilege but will ask the parties to brief whether it is "ex parte".  
Attorney Lettenberger to file his Brief by January 4th.  
Attorney Navis to file Response Brief by January 11th. 
 If the State choses to also file a Brief, their deadline would also be January 11th.  
Court schedules Motion for further hearing.  
9:55 a.m.  Court in recess.  Minutes filed.  Motion hearing scheduled for January 21, 2016 at 02:30 pm.

2:30 p.m.  Court in session.  Case Called.  
Defendant Justin W Prescott in court, in custody with attorney Francis R. Lettenberger.  
Diane M. Donohoo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Matter is before the Court on Defendant's Motion to Modify Conditions of Probation.   
Argument by Attorney Lettenberger.  
He believes the Jail on its own can allow release privileges or not even if the Court has said otherwise.  
Attorney Donohoo is not sure she is the right person to be here for this hearing.  
She believes Corporation Counsel or perhaps the Jail or DOC should be present in Court.  
Continued argument by Attorney Lettenberger.  
Court believes Corporation Counsel would be the appropriate party to respond to this.
Court will reset this to another Court date and ask that Corporation Counsel be served with a copy of the Motion.   
Attorney Donohoo believes the Defendant may need to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  
Response by Attorney Lettenberger.  
Court believes what the Motion document is "titled" is not what is controlling.  
Court will reschedule this hearing and will send a copy of the Motion down to Corporation Counsel.  
Motion hearing rescheduled to November 24, 2015 at 4:00 p.m.
